//@version=5
// ============================================================================
// DchannelBot — TradingView port of the LIVE strategy
//   Source of truth: src/deltabot/strategy/dchannel.py + dchannel_trader.py,
//   cross-checked against scripts/backtest_dchannel.py.
//   DEPLOYED config (dchannelbot, since 2026-07-12): 5-minute chart, Donchian(20)
//   + open==high/low confirm on synthetic Heikin Ashi, Williams %R gate OFF
//   (hunts on every DC touch), "highest_touch" anchor (re-anchors to the MOST
//   extreme band-touching candle, no ratchet-reset), day boundary 17:30 IST,
//   EOD square-off 17:25 IST, target premium ~1000, -70% option TP, weekend
//   (Sat+Sun) new-entry block.
//
// 2026-07-14 UPDATE #1 (confirm filter): the confirming candle NO LONGER needs
//   its own HA close above/below EMA(200). That single-EMA close check is
//   REPLACED by a persistent trend gate: BUY needs EMA(50) > EMA(200); SELL
//   needs EMA(50) < EMA(200) (both EMAs on HA close).
//
// 2026-07-14 UPDATE #2 (trailing SL, replaces the option TP): there is NO
//   take-profit at all -- the -70% option-premium TP is REMOVED. The SL
//   starts FIXED at the signal range's opposite extreme (as always) and
//   STAYS FIXED there while the EMA relationship remains favorable (the same
//   condition required to enter). It arms trailing ONCE -- on the exact bar
//   EMA(50) actually CROSSES to the UNFAVORABLE side of EMA(200) (a reversal
//   EVENT, not a continuous condition) -- and from that bar onward, EVERY
//   bar for the rest of the trade, SL := max(current SL, EMA(200)) for a
//   long / min(current SL, EMA(200)) for a short -- ratchets toward
//   EMA(200), never loosens, and stays armed even if EMA(50) flips back
//   favorable afterward. Before that first reversal cross, the SL never
//   moves at all. This mirrors this codebase's HeikinAshi bot's arm/tighten
//   pattern (max(existing, trail level), only ever tightens), but the ARMING
//   trigger here is specifically the adverse crossover event, not "while
//   favorable". (SUPERSEDED: the trailing SL was later replaced by a hard
//   close on the reversal cross -- see UPDATE #5. EOD removed -- see #4.)
//
// 2026-07-15 UPDATE #3 (hunt trigger, supersedes part of UPDATE #1): a new
//   signal search no longer runs continuously in both directions. It ARMS
//   only on the discrete event EMA(50) crosses EMA(200) -- crossing ABOVE
//   arms a BUY hunt (cancels any bear hunt in progress), crossing BELOW arms
//   a SELL hunt (cancels any bull hunt). From there the touch + open==extreme
//   confirm pattern proceeds exactly as before, but the confirm candle no
//   longer re-checks the EMA relationship on its own (the arming cross
//   already established it) -- CONFIRM is now pure price-action: touch the
//   DC band, then a candle with HA open == that extreme. Evaluated every bar
//   (not just while flat) so a cross that happens mid-trade still arms the
//   next hunt the instant the position goes flat.
//
// 2026-07-15 UPDATE #4 (no EOD close): the 17:25 daily square-off no longer
//   closes an open position. The 17:25-17:30 settlement window still blocks
//   NEW entries and cancels any un-triggered pending setup -- it just never
//   force-closes a live trade anymore.
//
// 2026-07-15 UPDATE #5 (exit = SL or EMA reversal cross, supersedes the
//   UPDATE #2 trailing SL): the arm-once trailing stop is REMOVED. A trade
//   now exits in exactly two ways -- (a) the FIXED signal-range SL (range low
//   for a long, range high for a short, never moves), or (b) a hard close at
//   MARKET the instant EMA(50) crosses to the unfavorable side of EMA(200)
//   (below for a long, above for a short), in profit or loss. This guarantees
//   a trade always closes on the trend reversal instead of running open
//   indefinitely while price never returns to a far SL.
//
// 2026-07-15 BUGFIX #6 (SL fired above the range low): the SL level (longStop/
//   shortStop) is now pinned at CONFIRMATION time, not at entry. Previously the
//   resting-breakout-order path placed the entry without setting the stop, and
//   because the exit block runs before the entry block each bar, a fill via that
//   resting order was checked against a STALE stop from a prior trade -- so a
//   trade could "stop out" at a price the current signal range never reached.
//   Also cancels the resting order when a setup is invalidated pre-trigger.
//
// 2026-07-15 UPDATE #7 (re-hunt after pre-entry invalidation): when a pending
//   setup dies because price hit its SL side before the trigger, the hunt for
//   that same direction RE-ARMS immediately (guarded: only while EMA(50) is
//   still on the favorable side of EMA(200)) instead of waiting for the next
//   EMA crossover. Because invalidation is processed before the hunt machine
//   on the same bar, the invalidation candle ITSELF counts: if it touches the
//   DC band, it becomes the anchor/start of the next signal range.
//
// 2026-07-15 UPDATE #8 (re-hunt after SL exit): an SL exit no longer consumes
//   the whole trend. If EMA(50) is still on the favorable side of EMA(200)
//   when the SL fires, the same-direction hunt re-arms -- but the SL bar
//   itself never counts as the touch (justClosedSL), so a FRESH DC-band touch
//   from the next bar onward is required to start the new signal range.
//   Combined with UPDATE #7, multiple signals per crossover are now possible;
//   the only thing that ends a direction's hunting is the opposite EMA cross.
//
// 2026-07-15 UPDATE #9 (state-based hunting, supersedes UPDATE #3's crossover-
//   event arming and subsumes the #7/#8 re-arm patches): the hunt is armed by
//   the EMA RELATIONSHIP itself -- while EMA(50) > EMA(200) the BUY hunt is
//   armed, while EMA(50) < EMA(200) the SELL hunt is armed. Fixes signals
//   silently not forming when the cross happened long ago / off-chart, or
//   after the daily 17:25 gap cleared the hunt state. Exits are unchanged
//   (fixed SL, or hard close on the reversal CROSS event). justClosedSL still
//   forces a fresh DC touch after an SL exit.
//
// HONESTY CHECK: this exact trailing-SL design has NOT been backtested.
// Treat this script as unvalidated until backtested.
//
// What the live bot does (and what this script mirrors):
//   * CHART BASIS: synthetic Heikin Ashi, fetched via
//     request.security(ticker.heikinashi(...)) so the pattern is correct
//     regardless of your chart's own candle style. Pattern LEVELS (trigger,
//     SL, EMAs) come from HA; whether price actually CROSSES those levels
//     (entry fill, invalidation, SL) is always checked against REAL price.
//   * DONCHIAN(20) on HA, PRIOR 20 closed bars (current bar excluded).
//   * ANCHOR ("highest_touch"): a candle whose HA extreme touches the DC band
//     starts a signal range. A LATER, MORE-extreme touch (lower high for bull,
//     higher low... i.e. bull re-anchors on a lower low, bear on a higher
//     high) RESETS the range to start fresh from it; anything else just widens
//     the existing range's high/low. No ratchet-by-%R (that legacy mode isn't
//     live).
//   * CONFIRM: a candle with HA open == HA extreme (bull: open==low, no lower
//     wick; bear: open==high, no upper wick). Direction was already decided
//     by the EMA crossover that armed the hunt (see UPDATE #3) -- no
//     per-candle EMA re-check. The signal range's final hi/lo includes this
//     candle.
//   * ENTRY: ASAP the instant REAL price breaks the signal range's far edge
//     (above the high for bull, below the low for bear).
//   * PRE-ENTRY INVALIDATION: if REAL price hits the range's near edge (the
//     stop side) before the trigger, the setup is discarded untraded.
//   * EXIT: (a) STOP-LOSS -- REAL price touching the signal range's opposite
//     extreme, FIXED for the life of the trade; or (b) EMA REVERSAL CROSS --
//     a hard close at market the instant EMA(50) crosses to the unfavorable
//     side of EMA(200) (see UPDATE #5). No TP, no EOD, no trailing.
//   * WILLIAMS %R(14) gate: OFF by default. When on, it's an ADDITIONAL
//     requirement at the moment of the EMA-cross arm (oversold for a BUY
//     arm, overbought for a SELL arm) -- it does not replace the crossover
//     trigger (this codebase's %R convention ranges 0..-100, never positive).
//   * WEEKEND BLOCK: new REAL entries are suppressed on Sat/Sun (matches the
//     live DELTA_SKIP_WEEKDAYS fix, 2026-07-14). The hunt/pending state
//     machine keeps running underneath -- exactly like the live engine, only
//     the final strategy.entry() is gated, so a setup armed on a blocked day
//     can still fire once an unblocked day arrives.
//   * NO EOD square-off (UPDATE #4): the 17:25-17:30 settlement gap blocks
//     new entries and cancels any pending (untriggered) setup, but does NOT
//     close a live position -- an open trade exits only on its SL.
//
// IMPORTANT — how the bot trades vs what this chart shows:
//   The bot SELLS options: bullish signal -> SELL a PUT, bearish -> SELL a
//   CALL. A sold PUT profits when BTC rises; a sold CALL profits when BTC
//   falls -- so on the BTC price chart the directional P&L is equivalent to
//   LONG (bullish) / SHORT (bearish), which is how this strategy maps them.
//   The bot's REAL take-profit is normally a -70% drop in the OPTION premium
//   -- this script REPLACES that entirely (per request) with two exits only:
//   the FIXED signal-range SL, or a hard close on the EMA(50)/EMA(200)
//   reversal cross (UPDATE #5). No separate TP, no EOD close, no trailing.
//
// LIMITATION — weekend block: live, a signal that completes on a blocked day
//   (Sat/Sun) still occupies the strategy's "in position" bookkeeping
//   internally (tracked against its own SL/EOD) even though no real order was
//   placed, which pauses new hunting until that phantom trade's SL would
//   have fired. This script does NOT replicate that pause -- it simply resumes
//   hunting immediately on the next bar. Only matters for setups that
//   specifically trigger ON a blocked day; does not affect weekday behavior.
// ============================================================================
strategy("DchannelBot — Bot-faithful Strategy (EMA50/200 gate variant)",
     overlay              = true,
     pyramiding           = 0,
     initial_capital      = 10000,
     default_qty_type     = strategy.fixed,
     default_qty_value    = 1,
     process_orders_on_close = true,
     calc_on_every_tick   = false,
     commission_type      = strategy.commission.percent,
     commission_value     = 0.0,
     max_lines_count      = 500,
     max_labels_count     = 500)

// ============================================================
// Inputs
// ============================================================
grpDC = "Donchian / Heikin Ashi"
dcPeriod = input.int(20, "Donchian Period", minval=2, group=grpDC)

grpEMA = "EMA Trend Gate (2026-07-14 update)"
emaTrendLen = input.int(50,  "EMA(50) length",  minval=1, group=grpEMA,
     tooltip="BUY needs EMA(this) > EMA(Long length); SELL needs EMA(this) < EMA(Long length). Replaces the old single close-vs-EMA(200) check.")
emaLongLen  = input.int(200, "EMA(200) length", minval=1, group=grpEMA)

grpWR = "Williams %R Gate (OFF matches live)"
useWR    = input.bool(false, "Require Williams %R oversold/overbought to arm a hunt", group=grpWR)
wrPeriod = input.int(14, "Williams %R Period", minval=1, group=grpWR)
wrLevel  = input.float(80.0, "Williams %R Level (arms bull below -level, bear above -(100-level))", group=grpWR)

grpDay = "Day Boundary / Square-Off (IST)"
dayTZ       = input.string("Asia/Kolkata", "Timezone", group=grpDay)
dayStartHr  = input.int(17, "New Day Start Hour",   minval=0, maxval=23, group=grpDay)
dayStartMin = input.int(30, "New Day Start Minute", minval=0, maxval=59, group=grpDay)
sqOffHr     = input.int(17, "Square-Off Hour",   minval=0, maxval=23, group=grpDay)
sqOffMin    = input.int(25, "Square-Off Minute", minval=0, maxval=59, group=grpDay)

grpFilter = "Day-of-Week Filter (matches live DELTA_SKIP_WEEKDAYS)"
skipSat = input.bool(true, "Block new entries on Saturday (IST)", group=grpFilter)
skipSun = input.bool(true, "Block new entries on Sunday (IST)",   group=grpFilter)

// ============================================================
// Synthetic Heikin Ashi OHLC (built-in TradingView HA ticker -- matches the
// Python formula exactly: ha_close=(o+h+l+c)/4, ha_open=(prevO+prevC)/2
// seeded (o+c)/2, ha_high/low = max/min(real, haOpen, haClose)).
// ============================================================
haData() =>
    [open, high, low, close]

[haOpen, haHigh, haLow, haClose] = request.security(ticker.heikinashi(syminfo.tickerid),
     timeframe.period, haData(), lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off)

plotcandle(haOpen, haHigh, haLow, haClose, title="Heikin Ashi",
     color = haClose >= haOpen ? color.new(color.green, 0) : color.new(color.red, 0),
     wickcolor = color.new(color.gray, 0),
     bordercolor = haClose >= haOpen ? color.new(color.green, 0) : color.new(color.red, 0))

// Tolerant equality for HA-derived open==extreme checks (matches the
// codebase's convention used in btc_heikinashi_strategy.pine).
eq(a, b) => math.abs(a - b) <= syminfo.mintick

// ============================================================
// Donchian(20) on HA, PRIOR closed bars only (current bar excluded via [1]).
// ============================================================
dcUpper = ta.highest(haHigh[1], dcPeriod)
dcLower = ta.lowest(haLow[1], dcPeriod)
plot(dcUpper, "Donchian Upper (prior 20)", color=color.new(color.purple, 0), linewidth=1)
plot(dcLower, "Donchian Lower (prior 20)", color=color.new(color.purple, 0), linewidth=1)

// ============================================================
// EMA trend gate (replaces the old close-vs-EMA200 confirm check)
// ============================================================
emaTrend = ta.ema(haClose, emaTrendLen)
emaLong  = ta.ema(haClose, emaLongLen)
plot(emaTrend, "EMA(trend/50)", color=color.new(color.aqua, 0),   linewidth=2)
plot(emaLong,  "EMA(long/200)", color=color.new(color.orange, 0), linewidth=2)

// Discrete cross events -- used ONLY for the exit-on-reversal close (section
// 1/2). Hunt arming is STATE-based (UPDATE #9), not cross-based.
crossedBull = ta.crossover(emaTrend, emaLong)    // EMA50 crosses ABOVE EMA200
crossedBear = ta.crossunder(emaTrend, emaLong)   // EMA50 crosses BELOW EMA200

// ============================================================
// Williams %R(14) on HA -- this codebase's convention: 0 = most overbought,
// -100 = most oversold (NEVER positive). Push-then-read (current bar included).
// ============================================================
wrHH = ta.highest(haHigh, wrPeriod)
wrLL = ta.lowest(haLow, wrPeriod)
wr   = wrHH != wrLL ? (wrHH - haClose) / (wrHH - wrLL) * -100.0 : na

// ============================================================
// Time windows: square-off 17:25, settlement gap 17:25-17:30, day-of-week
// ============================================================
sqMins   = sqOffHr * 60 + sqOffMin
sessMins = dayStartHr * 60 + dayStartMin
nowMins  = hour(time, dayTZ) * 60 + minute(time, dayTZ)
squareOff = not na(nowMins[1]) and nowMins >= sqMins and nowMins[1] < sqMins
inGap     = nowMins >= sqMins and nowMins < sessMins

dow = dayofweek(time, dayTZ)
dayBlocked = (skipSat and dow == dayofweek.saturday) or (skipSun and dow == dayofweek.sunday)

// ============================================================
// State machine — mirrors dchannel.py (hunt / touch / anchor / pending / SL)
// ============================================================
var bool  huntBull = false
var bool  huntBear = false
var bool  touchedBull = false
var bool  touchedBear = false
var float rangeHiBull = na
var float rangeLoBull = na
var float rangeHiBear = na
var float rangeLoBear = na
var float anchorLoBull = na
var float anchorHiBear = na

var bool  pendingLong = false
var bool  pendingShort = false
var float pendingTrigger = na
var float pendingSL = na
var float longStop = na
var float shortStop = na

// ----- 0. Settlement gap: cancel pending + clear hunts -----
if squareOff or inGap
    if pendingLong or pendingShort
        strategy.cancel("Long")
        strategy.cancel("Short")
    pendingLong := false
    pendingShort := false
    huntBull := false
    huntBear := false
    touchedBull := false
    touchedBear := false
    rangeHiBull := na
    rangeLoBull := na
    rangeHiBear := na
    rangeLoBear := na
    anchorLoBull := na
    anchorHiBear := na

// ----- 0.5. Hunt arming (2026-07-15 UPDATE #9, supersedes the crossover-event
//            arming): STATE-based, not event-based. While EMA(50) > EMA(200),
//            the BUY hunt is armed; while EMA(50) < EMA(200), the SELL hunt is
//            armed. This means hunting survives the daily 17:25 gap reset and
//            works even when the cross happened long ago / off-chart -- the
//            old event-based arming silently left the bot idle in exactly
//            those cases. The "not huntX" guard makes the reset fire only on
//            the transition, so an in-progress touch/range is never wiped
//            mid-hunt. Williams %R (if enabled) gates the arming transition.
if not squareOff and not inGap
    if emaTrend > emaLong and not huntBull and (not useWR or wr < -wrLevel)
        huntBull := true
        huntBear := false
        touchedBull := false
        touchedBear := false
        rangeHiBull := na
        rangeLoBull := na
        rangeHiBear := na
        rangeLoBear := na
        anchorLoBull := na
        anchorHiBear := na
    if emaTrend < emaLong and not huntBear and (not useWR or wr > -(100.0 - wrLevel))
        huntBear := true
        huntBull := false
        touchedBull := false
        touchedBear := false
        rangeHiBull := na
        rangeLoBull := na
        rangeHiBear := na
        rangeLoBear := na
        anchorLoBull := na
        anchorHiBear := na

// ----- 1/2. Exits (2026-07-15 UPDATE #5): exactly TWO ways out, no TP, no EOD.
//            (a) SL: real price touches the FIXED signal-range extreme
//                (range low for a long, range high for a short) -- never
//                moves for the life of the trade.
//            (b) EMA reversal cross: the instant EMA(50) crosses to the side
//                of EMA(200) that is against the position (crosses BELOW for
//                a long, ABOVE for a short), close at market -- whether in
//                profit or loss. No trailing, no waiting for price to come
//                back. This supersedes the old arm-once trailing SL. -----
justClosedSL = false   // resets false every bar; true only on the exact bar an SL fires
if strategy.position_size > 0
    if low <= longStop
        strategy.close("Long", comment="SL")
        justClosedSL := true
        // Re-hunting is automatic (UPDATE #9 state-based arming); justClosedSL
        // still forces a FRESH DC-low touch from the next bar onward.
    else if crossedBear   // EMA50 crosses BELOW EMA200: reversal against the long -> exit at market
        strategy.close("Long", comment="EMA cross")
if strategy.position_size < 0
    if high >= shortStop
        strategy.close("Short", comment="SL")
        justClosedSL := true
        // Re-hunting is automatic (UPDATE #9); fresh DC-high touch still required.
    else if crossedBull   // EMA50 crosses ABOVE EMA200: reversal against the short -> exit at market
        strategy.close("Short", comment="EMA cross")

// ----- 3. Breakout trigger for a PRIOR-armed pending setup (ASAP, real price).
//          Weekend block ONLY gates the real order here -- matches the live
//          engine, where the hunt/confirm machinery below is NOT weekday-aware,
//          only the final strategy.entry() placement is. -----
buyFired = false   // resets to false every bar; set true exactly when a BUY (Long) fires
sellFired = false  // resets to false every bar; set true exactly when a SELL (Short) fires
flatNow = strategy.position_size == 0
if flatNow and not squareOff and not inGap and pendingLong
    if high >= pendingTrigger
        if not dayBlocked
            strategy.entry("Long", strategy.long, stop=pendingTrigger)
            longStop := pendingSL
            buyFired := true
        pendingLong := false
    else if low <= pendingSL
        strategy.cancel("Long")   // kill any resting breakout order for this dead setup
        pendingLong := false      // invalidated before the trigger ever fired; hunting is
                                  // already re-armed (UPDATE #9), and section 4 runs after
                                  // this block on the SAME bar, so if this invalidation
                                  // candle touches the DC low it anchors the next range.
    else if not dayBlocked
        strategy.entry("Long", strategy.long, stop=pendingTrigger)   // resting order
else if flatNow and not squareOff and not inGap and pendingShort
    if low <= pendingTrigger
        if not dayBlocked
            strategy.entry("Short", strategy.short, stop=pendingTrigger)
            shortStop := pendingSL
            sellFired := true
        pendingShort := false
    else if high >= pendingSL
        strategy.cancel("Short")   // kill any resting breakout order for this dead setup
        pendingShort := false      // hunting already re-armed (UPDATE #9); same-bar DC-high
                                   // touch can anchor the next range (mirror of bull side).
    else if not dayBlocked
        strategy.entry("Short", strategy.short, stop=pendingTrigger)

// ----- 4. Hunt state machine (HA-based), only while flat/no pending/gates ok -----
// justClosedSL: after an SL, hunting is skipped for THIS bar so a fresh DC
// touch is required starting the NEXT bar (the SL-firing bar itself can never
// double as the re-touch) -- "if SL hit, wait for a candle to touch DC
// low/high again" per request.
// Hunt ARMING now happens in section 0.5 above (on the EMA crossover event);
// this section only progresses an already-armed hunt through touch -> confirm.
flatForHunt = strategy.position_size == 0 and not pendingLong and not pendingShort and not squareOff and not inGap and not justClosedSL
if flatForHunt
    // Bullish hunt progression.
    if huntBull and not na(dcLower)
        if not touchedBull
            if low <= dcLower
                touchedBull := true
                rangeHiBull := haHigh
                rangeLoBull := haLow
                anchorLoBull := haLow
        else
            reanchorBull = low <= dcLower and haLow < anchorLoBull
            if reanchorBull
                rangeHiBull := haHigh
                rangeLoBull := haLow
                anchorLoBull := haLow
            else
                rangeHiBull := math.max(rangeHiBull, haHigh)
                rangeLoBull := math.min(rangeLoBull, haLow)
            // CONFIRM (2026-07-15 update): open==low shape only -- direction
            // was already decided by the EMA crossover that armed this hunt,
            // so no per-candle EMA re-check here.
            if eq(haOpen, haLow)
                pendingLong := true
                pendingTrigger := rangeHiBull
                pendingSL := rangeLoBull
                longStop := rangeLoBull   // pin the SL NOW (bugfix 2026-07-15):
                                          // the exit check runs before section 3,
                                          // so if the entry fills via the resting
                                          // stop order, longStop must already hold
                                          // THIS range's low, not a stale prior one.
                huntBull := false
                touchedBull := false
                rangeHiBull := na
                rangeLoBull := na
                anchorLoBull := na

    // Bearish hunt progression (mirror).
    if huntBear and not na(dcUpper)
        if not touchedBear
            if high >= dcUpper
                touchedBear := true
                rangeHiBear := haHigh
                rangeLoBear := haLow
                anchorHiBear := haHigh
        else
            reanchorBear = high >= dcUpper and haHigh > anchorHiBear
            if reanchorBear
                rangeHiBear := haHigh
                rangeLoBear := haLow
                anchorHiBear := haHigh
            else
                rangeHiBear := math.max(rangeHiBear, haHigh)
                rangeLoBear := math.min(rangeLoBear, haLow)
            // CONFIRM: open==high shape only -- see bull-side comment above.
            if eq(haOpen, haHigh)
                pendingShort := true
                pendingTrigger := rangeLoBear
                pendingSL := rangeHiBear
                shortStop := rangeHiBear   // pin the SL NOW (bugfix 2026-07-15): see
                                           // the bull-side note -- prevents a stale
                                           // shortStop from a prior trade firing early.
                huntBear := false
                touchedBear := false
                rangeHiBear := na
                rangeLoBear := na
                anchorHiBear := na

// ============================================================
// Plotting / markers
// ============================================================
// Small markers when a setup ARMS (signal range confirmed, waiting for the trigger break).
plotshape(pendingLong  and pendingLong[1]  != pendingLong,  "Armed Buy",  shape.triangleup,   location.belowbar, color.new(color.green, 0), size=size.tiny)
plotshape(pendingShort and pendingShort[1] != pendingShort, "Armed Sell", shape.triangledown, location.abovebar, color.new(color.red,   0), size=size.tiny)

// Prominent labeled markers exactly when a trade FIRES (both directions).
plotshape(buyFired,  title="BUY SIGNAL",  style=shape.triangleup,   location=location.belowbar,
     color=color.new(color.green, 0), size=size.small, text="BUY")
plotshape(sellFired, title="SELL SIGNAL", style=shape.triangledown, location=location.abovebar,
     color=color.new(color.red, 0),   size=size.small, text="SELL")
bgcolor(inGap ? color.new(color.gray, 90) : na, title="Settlement gap")
bgcolor(dayBlocked ? color.new(color.blue, 92) : na, title="Weekend block")

inPos    = strategy.position_size != 0
activeSL = strategy.position_size > 0 ? longStop : strategy.position_size < 0 ? shortStop : na
plot(inPos ? activeSL : na, "Active SL", color=color.red, style=plot.style_linebr, linewidth=2)
plot(inPos ? strategy.position_avg_price : na, "Entry", color=color.gray, style=plot.style_linebr, linewidth=1)

armed = (pendingLong or pendingShort) and not inPos
plot(armed ? pendingTrigger : na, "Pending Trigger", color=color.new(color.aqua, 0),   style=plot.style_circles, linewidth=2)
plot(armed ? pendingSL      : na, "Pending SL",      color=color.new(color.orange, 0), style=plot.style_circles, linewidth=2)
